Package: pilot-link
Version: 0.11.0
Revision: 1
###
Depends: libpng-shlibs, readline-shlibs, tcltk-shlibs, python | python-nox, %N-bin (= %v-%r), %N-shlibs (= %v-%r)
BuildDepends: fink (>= 0.9.9), libpng, readline, tcltk, tcltk-dev
BuildDependsOnly: true
###
Source: http://pilot-link.org/source/%n-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: 7548dac7b3c1a7b6eb41a82bdeddb101
###
Patch: %f.patch
###
ConfigureParams: --with-pic --enable-shared --enable-static --with-tcl=%p --without-itcl --with-tk=%p --with-java=/Library/Java/Home --with-python=%p --with-libiconv=%p --mandir=%i/share/man --infodir=%p/share/info --libexecdir=%p/lib
###
#InstallScript: <<
#  mkdir -p %i/lib
#  cp libpisock++/.libs/*.dylib %i/lib
#  make install prefix=%i
#<<
###
NoSetLDFLAGS: true
SetCFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
###
DocFiles: COPYING* README
###
Splitoff: <<
  Package: %N-shlibs
  Suggests: %N-bin
  Files: <<
    lib/libpisock.*.dylib 
    lib/libpisock++.*.dylib
  <<
  DocFiles: COPYING* ChangeLog README
<<
Splitoff2: <<
  Package: %N-bin
  Depends: %N-shlibs (= %v-%r)
  Files: <<
    bin
    share/man
    share/pilot-link
  <<
  DocFiles: COPYING* ChangeLog README
<<
###
Description: Palm libraries                             
DescDetail: <<
Pilot-Link is the tools and toys needed to connect your Palm or Palm
compatible handheld (including Handspring, Sony, and Palm) with Unix
and Linux machines.
<<
DescPort: <<
Had to disable tcl/tk support till the maintainer of either x11 or tcltk
fixes a header file.
<<
